### Deliverable #1: Notion metadata schema

**Purpose:** Standardize content tracking, review workflows, and publishing signals across all Notion pages.

### Core properties (add to every content page)

- **Module ID** (text): Unique identifier, e.g., `FG-001`, `MOD-Jurisdiction-TX-002`
- **Version** (text): Semantic version, e.g., `1.0.0`, `1.1.0-draft`
- **Status** (select): `Draft` | `Review` | `Ready for Publish` | `Published` | `Archived`
- **Jurisdiction** (multi-select): `Federal`, `TX`, `CA`, `NY`, etc.
- **Author** (person): Primary author or contributor
- **Last Reviewed** (date): Last editorial review or sign-off date
- **Privacy** (select): `Public` | `Internal` (blocks export if Internal)
- **Provenance Notes** (text): Short description of intent, changes, or context for this version

### Optional properties (for advanced tracking)

- **Steward** (person): Local steward or jurisdiction owner
- **Related Modules** (relation): Links to other Notion pages
- **Changelog URL** (url): Link to GitHub commit or release
- **Export Timestamp** (date): Auto-populated by export script

---

### Deliverable #2: Provenance template

**Purpose:** Append to every published artifact (Markdown file) to preserve accountability and traceability.

```markdown
---
## Provenance

**Module ID:** [Module ID from Notion]  
**Version:** [Version from Notion]  
**Author:** [Author name]  
**Last Reviewed:** [Last Reviewed date]  
**Published:** [Export timestamp]  
**Notion Source:** [Notion page URL or ID]  
**Intent Declaration:** [One-line statement from Provenance Notes]  
**Repository:** https://github.com/[org]/[repo]  
**License:** [License type, e.g., CC BY-SA 4.0]  

*This document is part of the Judicial Forkwatch Coalition. It is not legal advice. For official guidance, consult a licensed attorney in your jurisdiction.*

---

```

